I just took it as kids in love.

207
00:10:44,701 --> 00:10:46,283
Did you ever hear of a guy named Max?

208
00:10:46,283 --> 00:10:47,932
Oh, you bet I did.

209
00:10:47,932 --> 00:10:50,902
That jerk came to my house!

210
00:10:52,580 --> 00:10:56,034
Don't forget to call before you go to sleep.

211
00:10:56,260 --> 00:10:59,436
What? 
You tummy hurt?

212
00:10:59,436 --> 00:11:01,288
No. I don't know.

213
00:11:01,288 --> 00:11:05,058
- Need me to stay home, baby?
- No, Mom, go.

214
00:11:10,031 --> 00:11:13,820
Uh... Good evening.

215
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:15,039
Yes?

216
00:11:15,039 --> 00:11:17,234
Is Eve here?

217
00:11:17,234 --> 00:11:18,152
Who are you?

218
00:11:18,152 --> 00:11:20,366
I'm Max... Tanning.

219
00:11:20,366 --> 00:11:21,842
Well, turn around Max.

220
00:11:21,842 --> 00:11:22,755
Mom!

221
00:11:22,755 --> 00:11:24,233
How old are you?

222
00:11:24,233 --> 00:11:25,115
Um...

223
00:11:25,297 --> 00:11:27,862
'cause she's 15!

224
00:11:27,862 --> 00:11:31,077
Ok, no harm, no foul.

225
00:11:31,077 --> 00:11:33,293
Walk away.

226
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:37,639
Mother!

227
00:11:39,669 --> 00:11:41,217
You can wait makeup... / Why?

228
00:11:41,217 --> 00:11:43,218
You don't know how you look to the world!

229
00:11:43,218 --> 00:11:44,580
What are you talking about?

230
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:45,574
'Cause you're young.

231
00:11:45,574 --> 00:11:49,091
But not so young that people 
don't see you and think things.

232
00:11:49,091 --> 00:11:50,887
- I can handle it, Mom.
- And want things.

233
00:11:50,887 --> 00:11:54,403
- You don't even understand.
- I can handle it!

234
00:11:56,562 --> 00:11:58,426
Did Mark know about this guy?

235
00:11:58,426 --> 00:11:59,926
I don't know.

236
00:11:59,926 --> 00:12:02,808
There was a lot 
I didn't know with Eve.

237
00:12:02,808 --> 00:12:05,475
She was in that hard teenage stage.

238
00:12:05,475 --> 00:12:07,442
I'm familiar.

239
00:12:07,442 --> 00:12:14,349
I was just waiting till 
she got... to her twenties.

240
00:12:14,349 --> 00:12:16,294
We could be friends again.

241
00:12:16,294 --> 00:12:17,787
Right.

242
00:12:19,555 --> 00:12:22,702
But we never got there.

243
00:12:25,879 --> 00:12:27,757
If I'm 15-year-old girl,

244
00:12:27,757 --> 00:12:29,667
why do I need $200?

245
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:31,936
And why not get it from 
the rich boyfriend?

246
00:12:31,936 --> 00:12:34,310
Maybe it had something 
to do with this older guy.

247
00:12:34,310 --> 00:12:36,467
You mean some she didn't 
want Mark knowing about?

248
00:12:36,467 --> 00:12:40,245
